<%# src/views/partials/badge-art.ejs
    Issue #410: the SINGLE place that decides how a badge's art_path renders.
    Every badge-display call site (guest task card, task-detail earn line,
    badge-earned modal, badge detail page, guest home, leaderboard,
    public profile, admin task board) includes this instead of hand-writing
    its own <img>, so "how does a badge look" has one owner instead of
    drifting per page.

    A task badge's art_path is a BARE bundled icon (no ring of its own —
    src/services/badge-icons.js is the catalog that produced it and the
    single owner of its path format; this partial asks that module's
    badgeIsIcon() local, not a hardcoded prefix, whether a given art_path is
    one). A system/auto/special/metric/transferable badge's art_path is its
    own fully composed circle SVG (e.g. /badges/garden.svg) and must render
    exactly as before — untouched pixels, no double ring.

    Locals:
      badge    (required) - { name, art_path } (task-badges.toTaskBadgeView's
                 shape, or any badges-table row projected the same way).
      alt      (optional) - alt text; defaults to badge.name.
      imgClass (optional) - class for the plain <img> rendered for a
                 composed/system badge (art_path not a bundled icon).
                 Defaults to 'badge-art', the class every existing composed-
                 badge call site already used, so an omitted local renders
                 byte-for-byte what that call site rendered before this
                 partial existed.
      width, height (optional) - width/height attributes for the plain
                 <img> branch only. The medallion branch is sized entirely
                 by CSS (ancestor-scoped .badge-medallion overrides, same
                 pattern the codebase already uses for .badge-art), because a
                 <span> wrapper has no intrinsic image dimensions to set.

    Sizing an icon-in-ring badge at a new call site: add a
    "<ancestor> .badge-medallion { width; height; border-width; box-shadow }"
    rule in theme.css (search "Badge medallion (#410)") rather than passing a
    size local here — this partial only decides WHICH shape renders, never
    how big.
%>
<% var badgeArtIcon = badge && badgeIsIcon(badge.art_path); %>
<% var badgeArtAlt = typeof alt !== 'undefined' ? alt : (badge ? badge.name : ''); %>
<% if (badgeArtIcon) { %>
  <span class="badge-medallion">
    <img class="badge-medallion-icon" src="<%= badge.art_path %>" alt="<%= badgeArtAlt %>" />
  </span>
<% } else { %>
  <img class="<%= typeof imgClass !== 'undefined' ? imgClass : 'badge-art' %>"
       src="<%= badge.art_path %>"
       alt="<%= badgeArtAlt %>"
       <% if (typeof width !== 'undefined') { %>width="<%= width %>" height="<%= height %>"<% } %> />
<% } %>
